Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:06.01,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.34,0:00:09.46,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.40,0:00:13.03,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough, Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.71,0:00:15.28,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.63,0:00:18.53,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What's going to happen on the surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.04,0:01:54.00,Episode-Title,sign,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Ten: \NThe Saltflake Snow Falls and Falls
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.36,0:01:56.51,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Now, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:01:59.25,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, the Sea God
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.25,0:02:03.72,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,was saddened by the humans who went up \Nto the surface and left the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:06.91,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,so he went into hiding far below \Ninto the depths of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.91,0:02:11.00,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,After that, saltflake snow fell and amassed\Nboth in the sea and on the surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.00,0:02:15.03,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,and the world gradually turned cold and gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.70,0:02:20.53,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Then one girl dove into the \Nsea to see the Sea God.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.28,0:02:24.23,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,She wanted to save the humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.23,0:02:27.84,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The Sea God's heart was \Nmoved by the girl's wish,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:30.54,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,and he joined the people once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.42,0:02:37.31,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,And now, it's not that the Sea God \Nkept himself from the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.31,0:02:41.05,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The people have forgotten about \Nthe Sea God, and moved away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.69,0:02:45.56,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Without prayers, the Sea \NGod loses his power...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.29,0:02:51.85,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to before, the Sea God's \Npower is much weaker and smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:54.06,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:56.32,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.32,0:02:57.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.52,0:02:58.82,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But it's a fairytale.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.82,0:03:02.74,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,This is the story of \Nhumans themselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.74,0:03:08.58,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Of the upcoming demise that will happen \Nin about fifty or a hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.58,0:03:10.08,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:12.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Upcoming demise? Humans?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.73,0:03:14.59,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You mean humans will die?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.59,0:03:18.12,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The only way that humans will survive
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.12,0:03:22.83,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,is if they can sleep and escape \Nthe upcoming freezing world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.83,0:03:24.22,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,"Sleep"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.73,0:03:28.81,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,From here on, the saltflake snow will \Ncontinue to fall and amass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.81,0:03:31.37,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The world will start freezing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:34.98,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,and people will not be able to bear \Nthe cold that will eventually come.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.98,0:03:39.04,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, we will go into a \Nlong sleep and let time pass,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.31,0:03:43.49,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,waiting until the Sea God is \Nable to regain his power.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.49,0:03:47.37,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,The people of Shioshishio \Nmust sleep immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.37,0:03:50.74,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,The longer we wait, \Nthe more people we will lose—
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.74,0:03:52.94,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Hold up! Wait, hold up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.94,0:03:55.69,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Are you both being serious right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.69,0:03:57.53,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Are you guys all right in the head?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.53,0:03:58.69,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.69,0:04:01.76,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we can \Nhibernate or anythin—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.76,0:04:02.63,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,We can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.99,0:04:05.94,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,The Ena that the Sea God \Nhas given all of you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.94,0:04:08.89,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,will let you sleep until \Nthe calamity has passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.29,0:04:11.74,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:13.16,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,This is all too sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.16,0:04:16.13,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We have school, and what \Nabout everyone of Oshiooshi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.13,0:04:17.42,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,The surface has nothing to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.68,0:04:20.59,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.59,0:04:22.41,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't obligated \Nto tell them anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.41,0:04:23.40,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.74,0:04:24.91,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:27.16,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You need to be prepared, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.93,0:04:42.84,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Like I can believe that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:49.35,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Manaka—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.93,0:04:52.26,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:14.89,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck? It's so messy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.47,0:05:40.92,Italics,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Her body was so warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.70,0:05:50.43,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, god damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.43,0:05:51.23,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.77,0:05:53.23,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.23,0:05:56.64,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,We will be having a feast with \Neveryone in Shioshishio on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:05:57.80,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,You need to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.80,0:05:58.54,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:01.47,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,If we fast, our Ena will thicken
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.47,0:06:03.57,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,and will be able to protect us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.57,0:06:05.96,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,And that is apparently how \Nthe sleep comes upon us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.69,0:06:09.72,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,So we are all eating to our \Nhearts' content one last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.72,0:06:12.58,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, children and \Nadults, will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.05,0:06:14.75,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,"Last"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.75,0:06:18.22,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You mean we're not supposed \Nto eat after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.22,0:06:19.47,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.16,0:06:26.50,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka, you need to\Napologize to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:28.51,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,He went out to look for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.12,0:06:30.36,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:31.78,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.78,0:06:33.37,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.37,0:06:35.35,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,You say that,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:39.32,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,but in order to thicken our Ena, soon \Nwe won't be able to eat anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.32,0:06:40.36,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.30,0:06:43.21,Main,mom,0000,0000,0000,,For crying out loud...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.98,0:06:49.15,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.20,0:06:51.93,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,But if we sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.93,0:06:53.70,Flashback-Italics,dad,0000,0000,0000,,They don't have Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.93,0:06:55.88,Flashback-Italics,dad,0000,0000,0000,,We aren't obligated \Nto tell them anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.88,0:06:58.51,Flashback-Italics,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,It's sparkly and pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.21,0:07:01.72,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.72,0:07:03.23,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.62,0:07:11.62,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.96,0:07:37.08,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.47,0:07:39.51,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,You're up early, Hikari.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.51,0:07:42.29,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't planning to head \N up to the surface, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.29,0:07:43.42,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.42,0:07:45.08,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,See? I'm not in my uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:46.48,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.99,0:07:49.05,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't leave Shishio.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:51.45,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just going for a walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.86,0:07:56.17,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be steaming some \Nseaweed for you on Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.17,0:07:57.41,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.41,0:08:01.95,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,He sure loves his seaweed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.32,0:08:08.05,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You did come after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:10.28,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "after all"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.28,0:08:12.55,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,We heard what happened from Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:13.70,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.70,0:08:15.16,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "What"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.42,0:08:17.55,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You were at Uroko-sama's, too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.61,0:08:23.06,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, what are you \Nguys going to do about school?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:24.81,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.81,0:08:27.14,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,If what Uroko-sama said is true,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.14,0:08:30.04,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,we have to tell everyone from Oshiooshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.42,0:08:33.20,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You think we have to tell \Neveryone on the surface?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.57,0:08:36.62,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But there's supposed to \Nbe no way to save them...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.62,0:08:39.79,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd be better\Noff not knowing then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.13,0:08:43.46,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,The people on the surface are \Ndifferent from us after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.46,0:08:44.92,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.92,0:08:47.07,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I think that some people \Nwould want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:48.44,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Like you-know-who.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:49.69,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,"You-know-who"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.69,0:08:51.76,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,You know he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.78,0:08:54.10,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.51,0:08:56.99,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,People meeting their demise or going to sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.99,0:09:00.57,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,supposedly comes down to the Sea God\Nnot having enough power, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.94,0:09:03.01,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That just means we really have to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.01,0:09:04.52,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,The Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.52,0:09:07.61,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,That's how we'll get the Sea \NGod to regain his strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.61,0:09:09.23,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,But they said it was canceled...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.23,0:09:11.02,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll talk to Uroko-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.02,0:09:13.17,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, it's not like we can
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.17,0:09:15.02,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,hear something this insane and be all, "Oh, okay."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.02,0:09:16.20,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We have to do what we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.20,0:09:17.04,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Hikari!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.04,0:09:18.02,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Wait right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.53,0:09:19.75,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,It's not happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.22,0:09:21.49,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,At least listen to what I have to say!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.29,0:09:23.58,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You seem desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.58,0:09:24.83,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.83,0:09:26.34,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,So what if I am desperate?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.34,0:09:32.05,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't you be better off if the \Nsea and the surface drew apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:32.71,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.88,0:09:36.91,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Being in love is a difficult situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.91,0:09:38.43,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.43,0:09:40.86,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Too much to bear, you can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.86,0:09:43.00,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You can't control yourself, to the extent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:45.33,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,that you're sad and in pain, \Nand your heart is full...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.33,0:09:46.17,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.17,0:09:47.37,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.37,0:09:49.22,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like you'd \Nunderstand how I feel!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.22,0:09:50.19,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,But I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.66,0:09:55.73,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,I am the scale of the Sea God who \Nfell in love with a human girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.73,0:09:59.45,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,A part of those feelings are within me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.08,0:10:01.53,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention, Hikari,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.53,0:10:05.24,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you're capable of swaying \Nthe feelings of the people of Oshiooshi.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.24,0:10:06.20,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.20,0:10:10.11,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Going through with the \NOfunehiki is not a small task.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.11,0:10:11.70,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,You should just give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.70,0:10:12.84,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.84,0:10:14.40,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to talk to them again!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.40,0:10:17.51,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You don't understand a \Nsingle thing about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.47,0:10:24.76,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,It's just till we go into the sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.76,0:10:26.02,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,What harm could it do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.80,0:10:29.86,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Why allow them to go \Nto school at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.86,0:10:30.98,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,Why else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:34.57,Main,uroko,0000,0000,0000,,It's compulsory education, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:45.83,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, are you listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.17,0:10:48.46,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You guys on the surface \Nshould do something, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:50.96,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Do you plan on not doing anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.96,0:10:54.93,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,You and Dad should have talked more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.93,0:10:58.27,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, that's not \Nthe point right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.27,0:11:01.47,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Aka-chan, are we going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.87,0:11:03.68,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.68,0:11:06.74,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, scaring \NMiuna-chan like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.74,0:11:07.96,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,But you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.96,0:11:11.89,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,we've been able to catch a lot of \Ngolden-eyes lately, and it's been cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.89,0:11:14.48,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of weird things \Nhave been happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.17,0:11:19.53,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,If weird phenomena keep happening \Nthe way Hikari-kun's saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:23.79,Main,itaru,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try to talk to everyone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.79,0:11:24.73,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:28.58,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think the guys from Oshiooshi \Nwill listen if it's me telling them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.91,0:11:31.54,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be doing the Ofunehiki \Nfor sure on our end.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.00,0:11:35.87,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Aka-chan, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.87,0:11:37.96,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.66,0:11:40.76,Main,akari,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be together forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.80,0:11:45.26,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.26,0:11:47.16,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,That's like super bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.16,0:11:48.17,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.17,0:11:50.53,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,I still want to go overseas, \Nget a boyfriend,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.53,0:11:52.52,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,and do a whole bunch of other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.52,0:11:54.48,Main,yama,0000,0000,0000,,I'd confess my feelings!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:55.69,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,To who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.69,0:11:56.78,Main,person,0000,0000,0000,,But you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.78,0:12:00.60,Main,person,0000,0000,0000,,if this happens after we \Ndie, does it really matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:03.65,Main,sayama,0000,0000,0000,,If everything were going to end \Ntomorrow, it'd be pretty big, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.65,0:12:04.60,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.60,0:12:07.80,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,You guys may be okay with it, but what \Nabout your grandkids and great-grandkids?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.80,0:12:09.62,Main,yama,0000,0000,0000,,"Grandkids"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.62,0:12:12.23,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,Our last resort is the Ofunehiki.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.23,0:12:14.88,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just some little \Nfestival anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:17.14,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,Kaname-kun, is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.14,0:12:19.16,Main,ki,0000,0000,0000,,Like everything being \Ndestroyed and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.39,0:12:20.98,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think he's lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.64,0:12:23.37,Main,egawa,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.37,0:12:24.89,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.89,0:12:29.37,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps has been saying \Nsomething's weird for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.05,0:12:32.92,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Like how the sea is completely \Ndifferent from before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.92,0:12:35.98,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,He said the sea probably won't \Ngo back to how it used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.42,0:12:44.65,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give the beaded ring to my mommy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.65,0:12:46.68,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,and I think Nyoppi to my Daddy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.49,0:12:52.02,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, give me your \Nstrawberry pencil, Miuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:55.15,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you my stationary with violets on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.15,0:12:57.50,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Sayu, aren't you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.50,0:12:58.91,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.91,0:13:01.78,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're distributing \Nmementos right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:04.35,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know when we're gonna die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.65,0:13:05.74,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.74,0:13:07.01,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to die, Sayu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.94,0:13:10.10,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die either.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:12.77,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,But there's nothing \Nwe can do. It's fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:14.57,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,But there has to be something!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.57,0:13:18.46,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,You and Aka-chan and Daddy are \Nall important and precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.46,0:13:22.00,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be something we can do so \Nall of my precious people don't go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.48,0:13:24.49,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.01,0:13:29.09,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Kaname... the people of the sea just \Nhave to sleep and they'll be fine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.09,0:13:31.45,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,But Aka-chan said she \Nwasn't going to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.45,0:13:33.50,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,She said she was going \Nto stay awake with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.50,0:13:37.92,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,But then, Aka-chan's going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.50,0:13:40.42,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,We can be together,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.42,0:13:43.81,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,but we'll be dead so we won't \Nbe able to see each other anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.81,0:13:44.76,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.07,0:13:51.96,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,I-I feel sick...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.96,0:13:53.23,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Sayu?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.66,0:13:54.98,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Miuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:59.62,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,How do you keep precious \Nthings precious?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.62,0:14:00.48,Main,miuna,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:05.48,Main,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,What happens when your \Nprecious things go away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:06.74,book_left,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,Mementos Distribution List\NKaname: Gloves and the \Nfour-leaf clover I found by Miuna's\NLong Hair: Sea Slug Pendant\NBoobs: Dolphin Pencil Board
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:06.74,book_right,sayu,0000,0000,0000,,This one deserves nothing!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.58,0:14:11.20,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.40,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what Shishio's been saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.00,0:14:16.10,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Gramps,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.66,0:14:20.57,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,do you think the saltflake snowfall\N and the cold is just temporary?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.57,0:14:23.83,Main,tsumu,0000,0000,0000,,Or do you think it's going to stay like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.50,0:14:26.01,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.22,0:14:31.85,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think it's something that can \Nbe helped within a single lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.85,0:14:34.57,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,Weather and environmental changes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.57,0:14:37.77,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,can be good or bad, depending on \Nhow the affected side sees it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.77,0:14:43.00,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,There might be something somewhere in \Nnature that is enjoying the saltflake snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.26,0:14:47.74,Main,gramps,0000,0000,0000,,It just happens that for \Nhumans, it was a bad change.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.19,0:15:03.16,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Does everyone have a drink now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.16,0:15:03.88,Main,guys,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:05.08,Main,guys,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.08,0:15:07.74,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Tomoru, you should say a few words.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.74,0:15:08.82,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.82,0:15:11.01,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Because you're the Chief Priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.01,0:15:12.18,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.83,0:15:13.64,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:14.82,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.01,0:15:19.48,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Thanks for...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:22.31,Main,dad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not good at this, but—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.15,0:15:22.41,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.41,0:15:23.73,Main,guys,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.20,0:15:36.67,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:41.46,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,The ends of rolled sushi are good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.08,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.08,0:15:45.21,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You've been weird since the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.21,0:15:46.45,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.80,0:15:49.49,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I've been normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.49,0:15:50.82,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take care of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.82,0:15:52.52,Main,Chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.52,0:15:56.18,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,Chisaki-chan, I have a favor to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.18,0:15:57.14,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.14,0:16:01.82,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,If you happen to wake up before I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.82,0:16:03.65,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,could you feed my sea rhododendrons?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.65,0:16:04.81,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Before?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:08.20,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,My late husband really loved those.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.20,0:16:11.15,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,If they were wilted when I \Nwoke up, he'd be very sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.15,0:16:14.25,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,If I wake up before you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.25,0:16:17.12,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make sure to take \Ncare of your plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.12,0:16:18.30,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.30,0:16:19.77,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.77,0:16:25.80,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,At my age, I don't even know if I'll\N be able to wake up after all this....
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:31.07,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't everyone going to sleep \Ntogether and waking up together?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.07,0:16:31.79,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.79,0:16:34.18,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,You mean that someone might \Nwake up before everyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:37.38,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,or everyone else might wake \Nup and someone might not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.38,0:16:38.74,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.74,0:16:41.37,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I think Uroko-sama will \Nprobably wake us up, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:42.32,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,When?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:44.76,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Probably after the saltflake snow stops
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.76,0:16:47.04,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,and people can survive again.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.04,0:16:47.90,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,So when is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.93,0:16:52.45,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,How would I know something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:55.29,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't ask Uroko-sama, Manaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.91,0:16:58.42,Main,grams,0000,0000,0000,,Chisaki-chan, where's the rolled sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.72,0:17:00.57,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'll bring it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.36,0:17:05.68,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,Why isn't Akari coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.68,0:17:07.15,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.15,0:17:09.79,Main,guy a,0000,0000,0000,,And I even steamed seaweed...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:15.05,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Why're you eating by \Nyourself like that, Manaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:16.78,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.78,0:17:19.76,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Shishio's future is all up to you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:21.41,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.41,0:17:23.12,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.12,0:17:24.40,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,When we wake up,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:28.06,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,the youngins need to be full of energy \Nto pop out kids left and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.06,0:17:29.52,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,"P-Pop"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:31.77,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter whose seed it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.77,0:17:33.33,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Make the babies.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.33,0:17:36.28,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Make babies from Shioshishio who have Ena!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.28,0:17:39.65,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,You need to work harder and fatten \Nup a little more, Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.65,0:17:41.49,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,You've still got a ways to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.01,0:17:43.70,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,This is the last. Drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.70,0:17:45.97,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Um... I'd prefer some tea...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.97,0:17:47.28,Main,guy,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, just drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.28,0:17:50.33,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I think you've had enough to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:52.67,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Look at you, Hikari, all grown up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.67,0:17:54.55,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drink this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:55.66,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Like hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.66,0:17:58.55,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,I'll drink it rather than let \Nsomeone like you have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.55,0:17:59.30,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.43,0:18:05.94,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,Don't believe what those \Nsurface people have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.94,0:18:07.97,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to go to the \Nsurface if I'm sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.97,0:18:08.94,Main,guy d,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.99,0:18:18.10,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Want some?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.61,0:18:21.49,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Chisaki made them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.26,0:18:26.39,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,They're really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:28.76,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.61,0:18:34.08,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,This doesn't feel real at all, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:35.15,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.63,0:18:39.76,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,But you know, this might \Nbe a dream right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.76,0:18:40.58,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.83,0:18:43.14,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,We might already be asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.44,0:18:47.69,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I might just be dreaming that I'm \Ntalking to you and eating rolled sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.17,0:18:49.37,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.73,0:18:51.25,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.73,0:18:53.14,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Just what I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.14,0:18:55.00,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You have bad taste, Kaname.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.84,0:18:58.36,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if I'll be able to wake up...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.92,0:19:03.00,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,What am I going to do if I wake \Nup and no one else is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.29,0:19:07.87,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,If we sleep, it might be the \Nlast time we see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:11.51,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I didn't have Ena.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.51,0:19:13.00,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Manaka...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:26.20,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:28.29,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.29,0:19:30.96,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Hikari will wake you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.96,0:19:34.90,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,But what if Hii-kun won't \Nbe able to wake up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.90,0:19:36.32,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.32,0:19:38.07,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,He never has any problems waking up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:39.45,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.45,0:19:42.76,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,He'll be the first one to wake \Nup and say, "I'm starving."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.76,0:19:46.32,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Not to mention if Kaname \Nor I wake up first,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.32,0:19:48.08,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,we'll definitely wake you up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.84,0:20:07.10,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(321,395)}I think you've had enough to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.72,0:20:12.61,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(363,1)}Just because our school closed,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.61,0:20:14.60,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,346)}doesn't mean the soul of Nami \NJunior High will disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:19.40,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(320,516)}I'll make it happen. The Ofunehiki!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:23.86,Flashback,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(320,221)}We'll find it no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.66,0:21:07.37,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you have to be red right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.46,0:21:23.71,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1,1179)}Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.64,0:21:33.37,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, Chisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.37,0:21:34.80,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What's up?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:36.51,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Why'd you come to get me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.51,0:21:39.36,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I'm done with just watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.36,0:21:40.51,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.05,0:21:45.01,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I thought it couldn't be helped while \Nyou were chasing after Hikari...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.47,0:21:47.56,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,But it appears we don't \Nreally have time anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.56,0:21:50.37,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kaname. What are \Nyou talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.37,0:21:53.51,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,I've liked you, Chisaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.82,0:21:55.08,Main,kaname,0000,0000,0000,,For quite a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.21,0:21:59.29,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.22,0:23:32.74,Main,itaru(?),0000,0000,0000,,You sure it's okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.74,0:23:33.97,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.97,0:23:34.56,Main,manaka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to eat, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.56,0:23:35.50,Main,chisa,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to get in trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.50,0:23:37.65,Main,weirdo,0000,0000,0000,,You saw, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.65,0:23:40.05,Main,hikari,0000,0000,0000,,We seriously are going to sleep...
